        <para>Example:</para>
        <para>For a 30 type Anchorlok double diaphragm spring brake, if dimension "B" (
            <hotlnk document="s04019_10.xml" xrefid="f0401912">Figure 12</hotlnk>) = 5.0 inches, setup stroke = 1 1/2
            inches (Stroke Value Table). The push rod length from mounting face to centerline of main clevis pin should
            measure: 5 - 1 1/2 = 3 1/2 inches with the spring brake caged (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401913">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0401913" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0401913" filename="../figg04/G0401913.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 13. Push Rod Length with Brake Caged</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark the push rod cut-off length. The length of the threaded rod protruding between the
                clevis legs must not exceed 3/16 inch to insure no interference with the operation of the slack
                adjuster.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Once the proper push rod length has been marked off, the push rod can be cut to length with
                the spring brake fully caged.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the clevis and jam nut on the push rod and mount the double diaphragm spring brake
                assembly to the mounting bracket. Tighten the mounting nuts to 105 - 125 ft-lbs. (142 - 169 N&#8226;m).
                The clevis must be adjusted so that it has full thread engagement on the push rod (from flush to 3/16
                inch protrusion).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the service and spring brake air lines to the proper air ports and the clevis to the
                slack adjuster and uncage the spring brake.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust the slack adjuster to the listed setup stroke. Refer to the Stroke Values table,
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl0401903">6.0.1.</hotlnk>. With the brake applied, the following conditions must occur:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push rod 90&#176; to the centerline of slack adjuster;</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push rod 90&#176; to the mounting face of the spring brake.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the setup results in the condition depicted in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401914">Figure 14</hotlnk>or
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401915">Figure 15</hotlnk>, the spring brake is misaligned and must be corrected by
                the following:
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spring Brake Misaligned (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401914">Figure 14</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401914" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401914" filename="../figg04/G0401914.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Spring Brake Misaligned</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Shorten push rod.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Align spring brake on mounting bracket.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spring Brake Misaligned (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401915">Figure 15</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401915" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401915" filename="../figg04/G0401915.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Spring Brake Misaligned</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lengthen push rod.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Align spring brake on mounting bracket.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Once the spring brake and push rod are set (
                <hotlnk document="s04019_10.xml" xrefid="f0401912">Figure 12</hotlnk>), release the brakes and adjust
                brakes. Refer to GROUP 04 - AIR BRAKES.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reassemble release tool in side pocket on spring brake chamber and install dust plug in
                release tool keyhole in center of chamber.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>After installation, check for proper spring brake operation, service operation and brake
                        adjustment.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
